[1] Eradication prospects
Date: Wed 26 Nov 2014
From: Steve Berger <steve@gideononline.com> [edited]


Although measles rates have declined dramatically during the past 4 decades, a recent upsurge reflects sub-optimal enforcement of vaccination in many countries. In the following graphs, I've summarized reported measles incidence and estimated vaccine uptake by region. http://www.GIDEONonline.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/MeaslesSummary.png.

Note that vaccination rates remain below 80 percent in 3 WHO regions (African, Eastern Mediterranean and Southeast Asian), while they exceed 90 percent in the other 3 (European, American and Western Pacific) [1,2]

References:
---------
[1] Berger S. Measles: Global Status, 2014. 415 pages, 537 graphs, 3376 references. Gideon e-books, http://www.gideononline.com/ebooks/disease/measles-global-status/.
[2] Berger S. Infectious Diseases of the World, 2014. 1333 pages, 397 graphs, 26 187 references. Gideon e-books, http://www.gideononline.com/ebooks/country/infectious-diseases-of-the-world/.

--
Steve Berger
Geographic Medicine, Tel Aviv Medical Center
<steve@gideononline.com>

[ProMED-mail thanks Steve Berger for providing these graphic illustrations of measles incidence and vaccination rates over the past 4 decades. The data are derived from the Gideon e-books. - Mod.CP]

