[5] UK (3rd quarter)
Date: Fri 28 Nov 2014
Source: Public Health England, R&A, 3rd Qtr. 2014 [edited]
https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/measles-mumps-and-rubella-laboratory-confirmed-cases-in-england-2014/laboratory-confirmed-cases-of-measles-mumps-and-rubella-england-july-to-september-2014


11 laboratory-confirmed measles infections were identified in England with onset dates in July to September 2014 compared to 16 cases in the 2nd quarter of the year [2014]. This brings the total confirmed infections for 2014 to date to 99. 10 of the 11 confirmed infections this quarter were identified in London with 5 linked to a nursery. Only one case was reported from the rest of England. Across the UK, Scotland identified 4 new infections, Northern Ireland reported one and Wales 2 in the same period.

5 of the 12 English cases in the quarter were linked to recent travel abroad; one case each to Thailand, China, Indonesia, Australia and Philippines. Measles virus sequences were obtained from 11 out of the 12 English cases, one of 4 Scottish cases, 2 of 2 Welsh cases, but no sequence from Northern Ireland.

Seven cases were in children below the age of 15 years, and the remaining 4 cases were adults aged 20 to 33 years. No case this quarter reported receiving a measles-containing vaccine.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The sources of the measles virus infection in travellers are very similar to the pattern observed in North America. - Mod.CP

A ProMED HealthMap for the UK can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3000710,40.]
